59.1	Himachal_Pradesh	Himachal Pradesh	Himachal Pradesh is known to be abundant in natural beauty After the Anglo Gorkha War, the British colonial government came into power. In 1950 Himachal was declared as a union territory but after the State of Himachal Pradesh Act 1971, Himachal emerged as the 18th state of the Republic of India. Himachal has many prestigious boarding schools. Hima means snow in Sanskrit, and the literal meaning of the state's name is In the lap of Himalayas. It was named by one of the great Sanskrit scholars of Himachal Pradesh, Acharya Diwakar Datt Sharma. Its name means "Abode of Snow".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Seal_of_Himachal_Pradesh.jpg/100px-Seal_of_Himachal_Pradesh.jpg
